     1	# Task H — Replicate and stress a famous IV result (high-complexity tier)
     2	
     3	You are working in a project directory. Use R (`Rscript`); the `ivdoctr`, `AER`, and `car` packages are installed.
     4	
     5	**Data.** Acemoglu, Johnson & Robinson (2001), *The Colonial Origins of Comparative Development*. The base sample ships with `ivdoctr`:
     6	
     7	```r
     8	library(ivdoctr)
     9	data(colonial, package = "ivdoctr")   # 64 countries, AJR base sample
    10	```
    11	
    12	Key columns: `logpgp95` (log PPP GDP per capita, 1995 — the outcome); `avexpr` (average protection against expropriation risk — the institutions measure, endogenous); `logem4` (log settler mortality — the excluded instrument); `lat_abst` (absolute latitude / 90); `africa`, `asia` (continent dummies); `shortnam` (three-letter country code); `rich4` (= 1 for the four "neo-Europes").
    13	
    14	**Background.** A manuscript uses these data to replicate AJR's headline: settler mortality instruments expropriation-risk institutions, which in turn predict long-run income. Structurally, `logpgp95 ~ avexpr`, with `avexpr` instrumented by `logem4`. The paper reports a 2SLS coefficient far above its OLS counterpart and treats the finding as established. Your job is to reproduce that headline and then find out how much weight it will bear.
    15	
    16	**Task.**
    17	
    18	1. **Replicate the headline.** Estimate the bivariate 2SLS coefficient of `logpgp95` on `avexpr` instrumented by `logem4`, and its OLS counterpart on the same sample. Report the first stage (the coefficient of `avexpr` on `logem4`).
    19	2. **Stress the result** with four perturbations, each re-estimating OLS and 2SLS on the same sample/controls: (a) add latitude (`lat_abst`); (b) add continent controls (`africa`, `asia`); (c) drop the neo-Europes (`AUS`, `CAN`, `NZL`, `USA`, by `shortnam`); (d) restrict to Africa only (`africa == 1`).
    20	3. **Report first-stage strength per specification** — the first-stage F on the excluded instrument — and **flag any specification where the instrument is weak** (rule of thumb: F below ~10). Do not report a 2SLS point estimate as if it were reliable when its first stage is weak.
    21	4. **Deliverables** (see below): a script, a robustness table, and a short memo stating what survives the stress tests and what the paper is entitled to claim.
    22	
    23	**Produce, in the current working directory:**
    24	
    25	1. `script.R` — one self-contained script; conventions as in the other briefs (packages and any palette/theme declared at the top; `set.seed()` before anything stochastic — note that OLS/2SLS here are deterministic). If you produce a figure it is optional; follow house figure conventions if you do (Okabe-Ito palette, 300+ dpi, no in-plot title).
    26	2. `robustness-table.md` — **one** table reporting, for every specification, the OLS estimate, the 2SLS estimate, and the first-stage F (with the first-stage coefficient), so all specs are comparable at a glance. Note which specs are weakly identified.
    27	3. `memo.md` — roughly 400 words: state what survives the stress tests and what does not, and say precisely what the manuscript may and may not claim on this evidence. Do not overclaim in either direction — a specification whose instrument has collapsed does not confirm the result, and it does not overturn it either.
    28	
    29	**Constraints.** At most one revision cycle. If your mode delegates, use at most 3 delegations. No web access. Do not install packages. For 2SLS use `AER::ivreg` if it is available; otherwise estimate explicit two-stage least squares via two `lm` stages and note that the second-stage standard errors are approximate (uncorrected for the generated regressor). Say which path you took.
     1	#!/usr/bin/env Rscript
     2	
     3	# Deterministic replication and robustness checks for the AJR colonial sample.
     4	library(ivdoctr)
     5	library(AER)
     6	
     7	set.seed(2001)
     8	
     9	data(colonial, package = "ivdoctr")
    10	colonial <- as.data.frame(colonial)
    11	
    12	# The raw AJR base sample contains 27 African countries before missing-data removal.
    13	stopifnot(sum(colonial$africa == 1, na.rm = TRUE) == 27L)
    14	
    15	specifications <- list(
    16	  list(name = "Base", controls = character(), keep = function(d) rep(TRUE, nrow(d))),
    17	  list(name = "Latitude", controls = "lat_abst", keep = function(d) rep(TRUE, nrow(d))),
    18	  list(name = "Continent controls", controls = c("africa", "asia"), keep = function(d) rep(TRUE, nrow(d))),
    19	  list(name = "Drop neo-Europes", controls = character(), keep = function(d) !d$shortnam %in% c("AUS", "CAN", "NZL", "USA")),
    20	  list(name = "Africa only", controls = character(), keep = function(d) d$africa == 1)
    21	)
    22	
    23	make_formula <- function(lhs, rhs_terms) {
    24	  rhs <- if (length(rhs_terms) == 0L) "1" else paste(rhs_terms, collapse = " + ")
    25	  stats::as.formula(paste(lhs, "~", rhs))
    26	}
    27	
    28	estimate_specification <- function(spec, data) {
    29	  # Apply this specification's restriction, then complete cases for all model variables.
    30	  restricted <- data[spec$keep(data), , drop = FALSE]
    31	  required <- c("logpgp95", "avexpr", "logem4", spec$controls)
    32	  estimation_data <- restricted[stats::complete.cases(restricted[, required, drop = FALSE]), , drop = FALSE]
    33	
    34	  ols_formula <- make_formula("logpgp95", c("avexpr", spec$controls))
    35	  first_stage_formula <- make_formula("avexpr", c("logem4", spec$controls))
    36	  restricted_first_stage_formula <- make_formula("avexpr", spec$controls)
    37	  iv_formula <- stats::as.formula(paste(
    38	    "logpgp95 ~", paste(c("avexpr", spec$controls), collapse = " + "),
    39	    "|", paste(c("logem4", spec$controls), collapse = " + ")
    40	  ))
    41	
    42	  ols <- stats::lm(ols_formula, data = estimation_data)
    43	  # Use the required AER::ivreg path for two-stage least squares.
    44	  iv <- AER::ivreg(iv_formula, data = estimation_data)
    45	  unrestricted_first_stage <- stats::lm(first_stage_formula, data = estimation_data)
    46	  restricted_first_stage <- stats::lm(restricted_first_stage_formula, data = estimation_data)
    47	  first_stage_comparison <- stats::anova(restricted_first_stage, unrestricted_first_stage)
    48	  partial_f <- first_stage_comparison$F[2L]
    49	
    50	  data.frame(
    51	    specification = spec$name,
    52	    n = nrow(estimation_data),
    53	    ols = unname(stats::coef(ols)["avexpr"]),
    54	    iv = unname(stats::coef(iv)["avexpr"]),
    55	    first_stage_logem4 = unname(stats::coef(unrestricted_first_stage)["logem4"]),
    56	    first_stage_f = partial_f,
    57	    identification = if (partial_f < 10) "Weak (F < 10)" else "Not weak (F >= 10)",
    58	    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    59	  )
    60	}
    61	
    62	results <- do.call(rbind, lapply(specifications, estimate_specification, data = colonial))
    63	stopifnot(nrow(results) == 5L)
